Install external software packages for BioTools

Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
* Install clustal, kalign and boxshade
* BLAST: 
    - Install blast+
    - Download NCBI BLAST databases from ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/blast/db/
* RDP: 
    - Download and extract rdp_classifier 
	from http://sourceforge.net/projects/rdp-classifier/
    - Set environment variable RDP_JAR_PATH to point to the jar or
	use Sys.setenv(RDP_JAR_PATH="/your_path/rdp_classifier-2.x.jar") in R

OS X:
* Install ClustalW from http://www.clustal.org/
* Install kalign from ???
* Boxshade is currenly not available for OS X 
  (you can compile it with free pascal compiler) 
* BLAST: Install blast+ 
  from ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/blast/executables/
* RDP: same as Linux

Windows:
* Download clustalw.exe, kalign.exe 
    (e.g., from http://www.tcoffee.org/Packages/Binaries/windows/)
* Boxshade is currenly not available for Windows
* BLAST: 
    - Download and install blast+ 
	from ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/blast/executables/LATEST/
    - Download NCBI BLAST databases 
	from ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/blast/db/
* RDP: see instructions for Linux

* Set path variable:
    - From the Desktop, right-click My Computer and click Properties.
    - Click Advanced System Settings link in the left column.
    - In the System Properties window click the Environment Variables button.
    - Add the folder with the executables to the path variable (separated by ;)
    - Try the following in R: Sys.which("clustalw")


